      "citation_id": "[CITATION_1]",
      "span_text": "Flap endonuclease-1 (FEN1) is a member of the Rad2 family of metallonucleases and is involved in several DNA repair and replication pathways, including the processing of Okazaki fragments during DNA replication, long-patch DNA base excision repair pathway, and rescue of stalled DNA replication forks that encounter DNA. These activities are important particularly at G-rich regions of telomeric DNA that are prone to form G-quadruplexes, which can stall replication forks at the ends of chromosomes. 2 FEN1 is highly conserved and has been demonstrated to play a critical role in both prokaryotes and eukaryotes."
